<%= render layout: "sessy/sources/layout", locals: { source: @source, active: :setup } do %>
  <div class="space-y-6 text-sm">
    <section class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 space-y-1">
      <p>Takes about 5 minutes. No AWS credentials shared with Sessy — you configure AWS to push events to your webhook URL. All events are cryptographically verified.</p>
      <p>
        New to SES?
        <%= link_to "Follow the full AWS SES setup guide", "https://github.com/marckohlbrugge/sessy/blob/main/docs/aws-ses-setup.md", target: "_blank", class: "underline" %>
        before continuing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Running in production?
        <%= link_to "Review security and deliverability best practices", "https://github.com/marckohlbrugge/sessy/blob/main/docs/ses-security-best-practices.md", target: "_blank", class: "underline" %>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 pt-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">1. Create a Configuration Set</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">A Configuration Set tracks what happens after emails are sent.</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1.5 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
        <li>Go to <strong>Amazon SES</strong> (correct region)</li>
        <li>Navigate to <strong>Configuration sets</strong></li>
        <li>Click <strong>Create set</strong></li>
        <li>Name: <code class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-white/5 px-1 font-mono"><%= config_set_name(@source) %></code></li>
        <li>Leave defaults, click <strong>Create set</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mt-3 mb-2">Prefer CLI?</p>
      <pre class="text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code class="language-shell" data-controller="highlight">aws ses create-configuration-set \
  --configuration-set '{"Name":"<%= config_set_name(@source) %>"}' \
  --region &lt;region&gt;</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 pt-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">2. Create an SNS Topic</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">SNS forwards events to your webhook.</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1.5 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
        <li>Go to <strong>Amazon SNS</strong></li>
        <li>Click <strong>Topics</strong> &rarr; <strong>Create topic</strong></li>
        <li>Select <strong>Standard</strong> (not FIFO)</li>
        <li>Name: <code class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-white/5 px-1 font-mono"><%= sns_topic_name(@source) %></code></li>
        <li>Click <strong>Create topic</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mt-3 mb-2">Prefer CLI?</p>
      <pre class="text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code class="language-shell" data-controller="highlight">aws sns create-topic \
  --name "<%= sns_topic_name(@source) %>" \
  --region &lt;region&gt;</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 pt-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">3. Subscribe the Webhook</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">Create an HTTPS subscription pointing to Sessy.</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1.5 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
        <li>From the SNS topic, click <strong>Create subscription</strong></li>
        <li>Protocol: <strong>HTTPS</strong></li>
        <li>Endpoint: <code class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-white/5 px-1 font-mono text-sm break-all"><%= webhook_url(source_token: @source.token) %></code></li>
        <li>Leave filter policy empty</li>
        <li>Leave <strong>"Enable raw message delivery"</strong> unchecked</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Create subscription</strong></li>
        <li>Confirmation is automatic</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mt-3 mb-2">Prefer CLI?</p>
      <pre class="text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code class="language-shell" data-controller="highlight">aws sns subscribe \
  --topic-arn arn:aws:sns:&lt;region&gt;:&lt;account-id&gt;:<%= sns_topic_name(@source) %> \
  --protocol https \
  --notification-endpoint "<%= webhook_url(source_token: @source.token) %>" \
  --region &lt;region&gt;</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 pt-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">4. Add an Event Destination</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">Connect your Configuration Set to SNS.</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1.5 text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
        <li>Go to <strong>SES &rarr; Configuration sets</strong></li>
        <li>Click <code class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-white/5 px-1 font-mono"><%= config_set_name(@source) %></code></li>
        <li><strong>Event destinations</strong> tab &rarr; <strong>Add destination</strong></li>
        <li>
          Select event types:
          <span class="text-zinc-400 dark:text-zinc-500">Sends, Deliveries, Bounces, Complaints, Opens, Clicks, Delivery delays, Rejections</span>
        </li>
        <li>Destination type: <strong>Amazon SNS</strong></li>
        <li>Topic: <code class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-white/5 px-1 font-mono"><%= sns_topic_name(@source) %></code></li>
        <li>Enable <strong>"Include original email headers"</strong></li>
        <li>Click <strong>Add destination</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mt-3 mb-2">Prefer CLI?</p>
      <pre class="text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code class="language-shell" data-controller="highlight">aws ses create-configuration-set-event-destination \
  --configuration-set-name "<%= config_set_name(@source) %>" \
  --event-destination '{
    "Name":"<%= sns_topic_name(@source) %>",
    "Enabled":true,
    "MatchingEventTypes":["bounce","click","complaint","delivery","deliveryDelay","open","reject","renderingFailure","send","subscription"],
    "SNSDestination":{"TopicARN":"arn:aws:sns:&lt;region&gt;:&lt;account-id&gt;:<%= sns_topic_name(@source) %>"}
  }' \
  --region &lt;region&gt;</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 pt-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">5. Use the Configuration Set</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-3">Specify your Configuration Set when sending emails.</p>

      <div>
        <p class="font-medium mb-2">
          With <%= link_to "aws-sdk-sesv2", "https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-ruby", target: "_blank", class: "underline" %>:
        </p>
        <pre class="text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code class="language-ruby" data-controller="highlight">ses.send_email(
  from_email_address: "you@example.com",
  destination: { to_addresses: ["user@example.com"] },
  content: { ... },
  configuration_set_name: "<%= config_set_name(@source) %>"
)</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-5">
        <p class="font-medium mb-2">
          With <%= link_to "aws-actionmailer-ses", "https://github.com/aws/aws-actionmailer-ses-ruby", target: "_blank", class: "underline" %>:
        </p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-2">Set globally:</p>
        <pre class="text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code class="language-ruby" data-controller="highlight">class ApplicationMailer < ActionMailer::Base
  default "X-SES-CONFIGURATION-SET" => "<%= config_set_name(@source) %>"
end</code></pre>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mt-4 mb-2">Or per mailer:</p>
        <pre class="text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code class="language-ruby" data-controller="highlight">class UserMailer < ApplicationMailer
  def welcome(user)
    headers["X-SES-CONFIGURATION-SET"] = "<%= config_set_name(@source) %>"
    mail(to: user.email, subject: "Welcome!")
  end
end</code></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 pt-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">Verify it works</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Send a test email with the Configuration Set. Events should appear in
        <%= link_to "Activity", source_events_path(@source), class: "underline" %> within seconds.
      </p>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mt-3 mb-2">CLI checks:</p>
      <pre class="text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code class="language-shell" data-controller="highlight">aws sns list-subscriptions-by-topic \
  --topic-arn arn:aws:sns:&lt;region&gt;:&lt;account-id&gt;:<%= sns_topic_name(@source) %> \
  --region &lt;region&gt;

aws ses describe-configuration-set \
  --configuration-set-name "<%= config_set_name(@source) %>" \
  --configuration-set-attribute-names eventDestinations \
  --region &lt;region&gt;</code></pre>
    </section>
  </div>
<% end %>
